  <rdf:Description rdf:about="http://ontology.amt.org/im#Industry">
    <rdfs:seeAlso rdf:resource="http://ontology.amt.org/views/industries#IndustryShape"/>
    <rdfs:seeAlso rdf:resource="http://ontology.amt.org/meta#CatalogValueShape"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://purl.org/nemo/gufo#Category"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <amtmeta:scopedBy rdf:resource="http://ontology.amt.org/views/industries"/>
    <rdfs:comment>Category (gufo:Category) classifying Company instances by industry. Rigid non-sortal: a Company's industry is a stable categorial identity rather than an aspect that comes and goes (contrast with im:Interest / im:ProductCategory, which are ExtrinsicModes). In this model, Industry instances are NOT materialized as distinct individuals — ind: Kinds serve as direct values of im:belongsTo, treated via OWL 2 punning as proxies for the categorial classification. Runtime value-space defined by ind_view:IndustryShape (collection membership) plus amtmeta:CatalogValueShape.</rdfs:comment>
    <rdfs:label>Industry</rdfs:label>
  </rdf:Description>
